<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="72" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,152,642]" pageId="10" pageNumber="72">
Valves rhomboid with a very slight constriction near rounded poles; 68.0–111.0 µm long, 17.5–21.0 µm wide. Striae with density of 
<quantity box="[416,521,190,216]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.858" metricValueMax="7.112" metricValueMin="6.604" pageId="10" pageNumber="72" unit="in" value="27.0" valueMax="28.0" valueMin="26.0">26–28 in</quantity>
<quantity box="[530,608,190,216]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="72" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 µm</quantity>
at valve centre, 
<quantity box="[806,867,190,216]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.112" pageId="10" pageNumber="72" unit="in" value="28.0">28 in</quantity>
<quantity box="[876,954,190,216]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="72" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 µm</quantity>
at valve ends. Striae mostly parallel but slightly convergent and sometimes wavy at apices (
<figureCitation box="[764,947,229,255]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–49" captionStartId="9.[151,258,1975,1996]" captionTargetBox="[304,1319,157,1959]" captionTargetId="figure-58@9.[304,1319,157,1959]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 41–49. LM. F. rexii. Valve views showing the size diminution series for the species. Figure 47 is the holotype. Figs 41–45. Specimens collected in Summer 1969. Figs. 46–49. Specimens collected in Summer 2008. Scale bars: 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4894862" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4894862/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="72">Figs 42 and 44</figureCitation>
). Externally, areolae lanceolate or round (
<figureCitation box="[159,335,268,294]" captionStart="FIGURES 50–55" captionStartId="10.[151,258,1864,1885]" captionTargetBox="[323,1263,700,1848]" captionTargetId="figure-355@10.[323,1263,700,1848]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 50–55. SEM. F. rexii. External and internal valve views of four specimens collected in the summer of 2008. Fig. 50, Full external valve view showing the strongly rhomboid valve shape. Fig. 51, Crescent moon shaped external distal raphe end. Fig. 52, External central area showing a grouping of small poroids and the crescent moon shaped raphe endings. Fig. 53. Full internal valve view showing the robust longitudinal rib system. Fig. 54. Internal valve apex with distinct and prominent porte-crayon structure and abruptly widened longitudinal ribs. Fig. 55. Internal central area with greatly constricted longitudinal ribs. Scale bars: Figs 50, 53: 10 µm; Figs 51–52, 55: 2 µm; Fig. 54: 1 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4894868" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4894868/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="72">Figs 51 and 52</figureCitation>
) with the most rounded areolae being located near valve centre (
<figureCitation box="[1090,1178,268,294]" captionStart="FIGURES 50–55" captionStartId="10.[151,258,1864,1885]" captionTargetBox="[323,1263,700,1848]" captionTargetId="figure-355@10.[323,1263,700,1848]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 50–55. SEM. F. rexii. External and internal valve views of four specimens collected in the summer of 2008. Fig. 50, Full external valve view showing the strongly rhomboid valve shape. Fig. 51, Crescent moon shaped external distal raphe end. Fig. 52, External central area showing a grouping of small poroids and the crescent moon shaped raphe endings. Fig. 53. Full internal valve view showing the robust longitudinal rib system. Fig. 54. Internal valve apex with distinct and prominent porte-crayon structure and abruptly widened longitudinal ribs. Fig. 55. Internal central area with greatly constricted longitudinal ribs. Scale bars: Figs 50, 53: 10 µm; Figs 51–52, 55: 2 µm; Fig. 54: 1 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4894868" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4894868/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="72">Fig. 52</figureCitation>
). Adjacent to external central area, areolae can be slightly expanded (
<figureCitation box="[702,846,306,332]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–49" captionStartId="9.[151,258,1975,1996]" captionTargetBox="[304,1319,157,1959]" captionTargetId="figure-58@9.[304,1319,157,1959]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 41–49. LM. F. rexii. Valve views showing the size diminution series for the species. Figure 47 is the holotype. Figs 41–45. Specimens collected in Summer 1969. Figs. 46–49. Specimens collected in Summer 2008. Scale bars: 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4894862" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4894862/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="72">Figs. 45, 46</figureCitation>
, and 52). Internally, areolar openings round (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 50–55" captionStartId="10.[151,258,1864,1885]" captionTargetBox="[323,1263,700,1848]" captionTargetId="figure-355@10.[323,1263,700,1848]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 50–55. SEM. F. rexii. External and internal valve views of four specimens collected in the summer of 2008. Fig. 50, Full external valve view showing the strongly rhomboid valve shape. Fig. 51, Crescent moon shaped external distal raphe end. Fig. 52, External central area showing a grouping of small poroids and the crescent moon shaped raphe endings. Fig. 53. Full internal valve view showing the robust longitudinal rib system. Fig. 54. Internal valve apex with distinct and prominent porte-crayon structure and abruptly widened longitudinal ribs. Fig. 55. Internal central area with greatly constricted longitudinal ribs. Scale bars: Figs 50, 53: 10 µm; Figs 51–52, 55: 2 µm; Fig. 54: 1 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4894868" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4894868/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="72">Figs 54 and 55</figureCitation>
). Areolae extend around apices, but striae greatly reduced (
<figureCitation box="[993,1082,345,371]" captionStart="FIGURES 50–55" captionStartId="10.[151,258,1864,1885]" captionTargetBox="[323,1263,700,1848]" captionTargetId="figure-355@10.[323,1263,700,1848]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 50–55. SEM. F. rexii. External and internal valve views of four specimens collected in the summer of 2008. Fig. 50, Full external valve view showing the strongly rhomboid valve shape. Fig. 51, Crescent moon shaped external distal raphe end. Fig. 52, External central area showing a grouping of small poroids and the crescent moon shaped raphe endings. Fig. 53. Full internal valve view showing the robust longitudinal rib system. Fig. 54. Internal valve apex with distinct and prominent porte-crayon structure and abruptly widened longitudinal ribs. Fig. 55. Internal central area with greatly constricted longitudinal ribs. Scale bars: Figs 50, 53: 10 µm; Figs 51–52, 55: 2 µm; Fig. 54: 1 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4894868" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4894868/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="72">Fig. 51</figureCitation>
). Longitudinal striae parallel over majority of valve but become slightly wavy at valve centre (
<figureCitation box="[960,1149,384,410]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–49" captionStartId="9.[151,258,1975,1996]" captionTargetBox="[304,1319,157,1959]" captionTargetId="figure-58@9.[304,1319,157,1959]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 41–49. LM. F. rexii. Valve views showing the size diminution series for the species. Figure 47 is the holotype. Figs 41–45. Specimens collected in Summer 1969. Figs. 46–49. Specimens collected in Summer 2008. Scale bars: 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4894862" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4894862/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="72">Figs 42 and 45</figureCitation>
). External central area possessing an irregular grouping of small poroids of varying number (
<figureCitation box="[980,1118,422,448]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–49" captionStartId="9.[151,258,1975,1996]" captionTargetBox="[304,1319,157,1959]" captionTargetId="figure-58@9.[304,1319,157,1959]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 41–49. LM. F. rexii. Valve views showing the size diminution series for the species. Figure 47 is the holotype. Figs 41–45. Specimens collected in Summer 1969. Figs. 46–49. Specimens collected in Summer 2008. Scale bars: 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4894862" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4894862/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="72">Figs 44, 47</figureCitation>
, and 52). Rows of areolae adjacent to either side of raphe terminate before distal raphe ending (
<figureCitation box="[951,1037,461,487]" captionStart="FIGURES 50–55" captionStartId="10.[151,258,1864,1885]" captionTargetBox="[323,1263,700,1848]" captionTargetId="figure-355@10.[323,1263,700,1848]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 50–55. SEM. F. rexii. External and internal valve views of four specimens collected in the summer of 2008. Fig. 50, Full external valve view showing the strongly rhomboid valve shape. Fig. 51, Crescent moon shaped external distal raphe end. Fig. 52, External central area showing a grouping of small poroids and the crescent moon shaped raphe endings. Fig. 53. Full internal valve view showing the robust longitudinal rib system. Fig. 54. Internal valve apex with distinct and prominent porte-crayon structure and abruptly widened longitudinal ribs. Fig. 55. Internal central area with greatly constricted longitudinal ribs. Scale bars: Figs 50, 53: 10 µm; Figs 51–52, 55: 2 µm; Fig. 54: 1 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4894868" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4894868/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="72">Fig. 51</figureCitation>
). Internal longitudinal ribs robust, widen significantly but smoothly at central area before constricting at central nodule (
<figureCitation box="[1230,1422,500,526]" captionStart="FIGURES 50–55" captionStartId="10.[151,258,1864,1885]" captionTargetBox="[323,1263,700,1848]" captionTargetId="figure-355@10.[323,1263,700,1848]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 50–55. SEM. F. rexii. External and internal valve views of four specimens collected in the summer of 2008. Fig. 50, Full external valve view showing the strongly rhomboid valve shape. Fig. 51, Crescent moon shaped external distal raphe end. Fig. 52, External central area showing a grouping of small poroids and the crescent moon shaped raphe endings. Fig. 53. Full internal valve view showing the robust longitudinal rib system. Fig. 54. Internal valve apex with distinct and prominent porte-crayon structure and abruptly widened longitudinal ribs. Fig. 55. Internal central area with greatly constricted longitudinal ribs. Scale bars: Figs 50, 53: 10 µm; Figs 51–52, 55: 2 µm; Fig. 54: 1 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4894868" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4894868/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="72">Figs 53 and 55</figureCitation>
). Longitudinal ribs widen very abruptly near apices, then terminate bluntly at helictoglossa (
<figureCitation box="[1241,1379,538,564]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–49" captionStartId="9.[151,258,1975,1996]" captionTargetBox="[304,1319,157,1959]" captionTargetId="figure-58@9.[304,1319,157,1959]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 41–49. LM. F. rexii. Valve views showing the size diminution series for the species. Figure 47 is the holotype. Figs 41–45. Specimens collected in Summer 1969. Figs. 46–49. Specimens collected in Summer 2008. Scale bars: 10 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4894862" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4894862/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="72">Figs 42, 45</figureCitation>
, and 53). Longitudinal ribs fuse with the linear helictoglossa to form a wide and prominent porte-crayon structure (
<figureCitation box="[159,247,616,642]" captionStart="FIGURES 50–55" captionStartId="10.[151,258,1864,1885]" captionTargetBox="[323,1263,700,1848]" captionTargetId="figure-355@10.[323,1263,700,1848]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 50–55. SEM. F. rexii. External and internal valve views of four specimens collected in the summer of 2008. Fig. 50, Full external valve view showing the strongly rhomboid valve shape. Fig. 51, Crescent moon shaped external distal raphe end. Fig. 52, External central area showing a grouping of small poroids and the crescent moon shaped raphe endings. Fig. 53. Full internal valve view showing the robust longitudinal rib system. Fig. 54. Internal valve apex with distinct and prominent porte-crayon structure and abruptly widened longitudinal ribs. Fig. 55. Internal central area with greatly constricted longitudinal ribs. Scale bars: Figs 50, 53: 10 µm; Figs 51–52, 55: 2 µm; Fig. 54: 1 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4894868" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4894868/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="72">Fig. 54</figureCitation>
). External proximal raphe ends expanded into shallow crescent-moon shapes (
